07/06/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Authorities released 14 people Friday (June 5th) detained in the latest wave of arrests in the Ergenekon investigation, media reported. They were among 20 people rounded up during simultaneous operations in five provinces last Thursday. The shadowy Ergenekon network is accused of having planned bombings and assassinations to incite chaos and overthrow the ruling Justice and Development Party's government. More than 200 people have been charged in connection with the Ergenekon case.
In other news Friday, the General Staff said six members of the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) were killed in a two-week military operation. Brigadier General Metin Gurak told a press briefing that seven other PKK members surrendered and one was captured. (CNNTurk, Anadolu news agency, Hurriyet, AKI, Xinhua - 05/06/09)
